vim: ft=markdown:et

 - Git supports an `encoding` header in commit messages
   iso8859-13 ok, gb18030 ok, iso-2022-jp ok
 - working:
    - giggle 0.7 -- ok
    - gitk -- ok
    - git -- ok (rebasing loses "encoding" header)
    - tig 1.1 -- ok
 - not working (local apps):
    - gitg 0.2.5 -- segfaults with -O2, same as GitHub/qgit otherwise
    - GitHub for Windows -- ignores header, uses utf-8, no fallback
                            (shows "invalid char" glyphs for iso8859)
    - qgit 2.3 -- ignores header, tries utf-8, always fallbacks to iso885901
 - not working (web apps):
    - BitBucket -- ignores header, tries utf-8, fallbacks to iso8859-2 (!?),
                   shows nothing for invalid chars (quietly discards)
    - GitHub -- ignores header, tries utf-8, always fallbacks to iso8859-1
    - Gitorious -- ignores header, uses utf-8, no fallback (shows "invalid char" glyphs)
